    <description>Plants loosely cespitose; rhizomes long, slender. Culms grooved, terete, 5–14 cm,
        smooth. Leaves: basal sheaths brown; distal leaf sheaths truncate to concave at mouth;
        blades 2–8.4 × 0.4–0.5 mm, much shorter than culms at flowering and fruiting.
        Inflorescences: spikelets 3–6-flowered, 3–4.6 × 1.7–2.8 mm; bracts shorter than spikelets,
        1.6–2.5 mm, apex mucronate. Spikelets: scales brown, apex obtuse. Flowers: perianth bristles
        absent; anthers 0.8–1.5 mm. Achenes compressed trigonous to plano-convex, (1.2–)1.4–1.9 ×
        0.8–1.2 mm.</description>
